The problem is here,
```
this.setState({
   countries: this.state.countries.filter(c =&gt; c.country === value)
});
```

Here you are filtering the `countries` array and storing it to the same. So when first time you filter your original `countries` array is gets changed and you only have filtered data. On next filter you are filtering data from previous result and not from original array.

You need to keep a copy of original data in a constructor,
```
constructor() {
    super();
    //This is initial state
